<TITLE> Case filed against CEC for 'hurting religious sentiment' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 25 (bdnews24.com) A criminal case has been lodged against the Chief election commissioner ATM Samsul Huda on charges of hurting religious sentiment. Mohammad Hossain Akand, a businessman of the capital's East Basabo area, filed the case with a Dhaka Chief Metropolitan Magistrate Court. The case papers claim that it was reported in newspapers on Apr 16, that the CEC at his residence had said in relation to the Bhola by-elections, "The armed forces are not divine beings that can fix everything. Forget the army, not even God can do everything." The case alleges that Huda had intentionally made this statement to challenge the Almighty's authority and hurt the religious sentiments of millions of Muslims living in the country. Magistrate AKM Emdadul Haque accepted the case but did not pass any order. bd
